      "location": "auth",
      "position": "after",
      "content": "## Auth\n\nThe Arcade Gmail MCP Server uses the [Google auth provider](/references/auth-providers/google) to connect to users' Google accounts.\n\n<Callout type=\"warning\">\n**Important**: Gmail access requires Google OAuth and specific scopes to read, modify, or send messages. Ensure your OAuth client is configured in the Google Cloud Console and the required scopes are approved for your project.\n</Callout>\n\n<Callout type=\"info\">\nSelf-hosted deployments must configure a valid OAuth consent screen and provide the correct redirect URIs. Cloud-hosted instances may use the built-in provider configuration.\n</Callout>\n\n**Permission summary:**\n- `https://www.googleapis.com/auth/gmail.readonly` — read messages and metadata\n- `https://www.googleapis.com/auth/gmail.modify` — read and modify (archive, label, delete)\n- `https://www.googleapis.com/auth/gmail.send` — send messages on behalf of the user\n- Additional scopes may be required for mailbox settings or full admin access\n\n**Setup notes / important limitations:**\n- Ensure the OAuth consent screen and scopes are accepted by Google; some scopes require verification.\n- For enterprise use, coordinate with Google Workspace admins to allow app access and domain-wide delegation if needed.\n- Avoid requesting broader scopes than necessary to reduce approval friction and security risk.",
      "header": "## Auth"
    }
  ],
  "customImports": [],
  "subPages": [],
  "generatedAt": "2026-01-26T17:31:27.246Z",
  "summary": "Arcade.dev's Gmail toolkit enables seamless integration with the Gmail API, allowing developers to manage emails and labels effectively within their applications.\n\n**Capabilities**\n- Manage email threads and labels.\n- Compose, send, and manage drafts.\n- Retrieve detailed user profile information.\n- Support for email searching and filtering.\n- Efficiently handle email status changes such as trashing.\n\n**OAuth**\n- **Provider**: Google\n- **Scopes**: Access to read, compose, modify, and send Gmail emails, alongside user profile information.\n\n**Secrets**\n- No secret types required for toolkit operation."
